As Jerrold Magtagnob wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/16/2004 at 09:53:51 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>In how many ways we could find the word triangles in this figure?
>                           T
>                          R R
>                         I I I
>                        A A A A
>                       N N N N N
>                        G G G G
>                         L L L
>                          E E
>                           S
>


You have to make a total of 8 steps of which 4 must be to the left 
and 4 to the right.  Number of paths

        8!
   =  -----  = C(8,4) =  70
      4! 4!

So there will be total of 70 different paths from top to bottom and 
this is the same as the number of ways of making the 
word 'triangles'.



